Sending a piece of my heart into the wild and I’m filled with so much gratitude.

Thank you for being here. Thank you for sharing your stories. Thank you for supporting my work. Happy Tuesday 🥰

New work and a few random thoughts as we begin another trip around the sun…

I’ve been seeing (as I’m sure you all have) all of the new year posts and promises. The goal setting and the achievements. The best views and the most beautiful creations. It took me sitting with these posts and my thoughts to begin to formulate an understanding of where I am in my own journey. 

So many things in this life are cyclical. Water, forests, rocks, trends, fashion, art (artists) and more each flow through continuous and cyclical change. It is natural. It is beautiful. It is necessary. 

Me? I’ve been in a resting phase. I’ve been quiet and observational. I’ve been a conservator of energy. I haven’t been focused on output and that is okay. That is beautiful. I’m still an artist. 

The cool part is, I can feel myself flowing through this stage. My energy and curiosity are building. Ideas are forming as inspiration builds. I’m beginning to understand where I want to go next and I’m so grateful to have you here with me as I discover and begin to share new work. Words , images, textures and colours are peaking my interest. Excitement is building. 

Excitement is building. 

Photos of my newest piece and some colours and textures that are beginning to stand out as I move through rest and begin to notice my surroundings again. What phase of life / art journey are you in right now? Is there anything trying about that phase you want to talk about? Anything beautiful you want to share? I’d love to hear 🥰

Happy New Year!
You’re right where you need to be ❤️

16x20” Watercolour on Arches Cold Pressed Cotton Paper

NEW COLLECTION ON ITS WAY

A new collection of originals will be released sometime this spring with framing options for collectors in North America (possibly worldwide). The series will embrace vibrant colours and will serve as a reminder of how powerful it is to speak your dreams aloud. Stay tuned for updates as o begin to paint!

Waterfalls and Winged Dreams

Suppose, for just a moment 
That you gave wings to your dreams
Rather than pinning them down with worry or dread
You let them fly instead

Suppose, for just a moment
That your head was in the clouds
Rather than swimming with worry and doubt
You spoke your dreams aloud

Suppose, for just a moment then,
That your heart began to soar
Rather than drowning with worry and fear
Your dreams had wings and you let them steer

-Karlyn Shahnazarian

New collection will be painted on @archespapers premium cotton cold pressed paper. #archespaper #archeswatercolorpaper #watercolourart

Framed Florals Available 🌸 

I’ve been working diligently on my newest collection and will have a new landscape to show you soon. 

In the meantime I wanted to celebrate these framed floral minis which are all available in my Etsy shop today. 

So many lovely ways to combine these pieces. Hand painted on @archespapers, treated with a matte wax and custom framed. Each frame comes with hardware (ready to hang) or the ability to stand on any shelf in need of some spring beauty. 

Shop originals and prints here:

https://etsy.me/3BbcuMm

This one’s for my local lovelies!
 
I’ve been quietly prepping for Spice Holiday Market this year. It’s a beautiful artisan market put on by local business owners celebrating local hand made goods. Each of the artisans has so much beauty to share and I’m excited to be able to do all of my Christmas shopping locally!

I think this will be my last market for a while so I’ve curated some fun and unique offerings this year! In addition to my original artwork and fine art prints, I will also have various art supply bundles. This one in particular comes with four blank watercolour cards, a watercolour brush and a curated holiday palette of my favourite paints on @archespapers for you to enjoy. 

I’m so excited to spread the joy of watercolour painting throughout Simcoe County. 

After this market I plan to focus a little bit more on my original artwork. I think there are some really exciting things on the horizon. 

Thank you for being on this journey with me. Your support means the world, truly. 

#archespaper #spiceholidaymarket #simcoecounty #artisanmarkets #ontariocanada #barrieontario

Holiday Ornament Sneak Peek 🌲 ❄️ 

I’ve fallen in love with my annual ornament process. Each year I go through discarded or imperfect paintings I’ve created throughout the year and I find my favourite parts. Those favourite parts get cut out and become tiny landscapes of their own. The process of finding beauty amongst my least favourite paintings helps me to remember that sometimes all that is needed is a fresh perspective. 

These tiny landscapes are painted on @archespapers and will be available @spiceholidaymarket December 1-2

Let me know below if you have a favourite already (and whether you think I should sell a few in my stories before the market 😉)!

Mark Your Calendars : Ornament Release Date is Sunday November 26th at 10:00 AM EST

I will be releasing a small batch of this year’s ornaments before my December market for all of my favourite humans here ❤️🌲 

There will be 14 original ornaments this year. Each original 1” x 1” is painted on @archespapers and framed in a handmade frame finished with hand dyed ribbon from @eucadesign 

I’m really excited about these and wish I had more to offer - but these hands can only move so quick!!

Hand Painted Ornaments Are Live!

5/14 Ornaments are left 🎄 
See my stories today for details!
